column2: Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
Spiny waterflea sample was collected with Ekman dredge method. 5 aliquots examined; sediments were mostly very fine material that passed through the sieve.
Water level visually assessed as high. Deep hole depth 7.7 feet. Water sample was taken by hand grab. Meter not calibrated before monitoring. Monitored at 43.54494- -89.10493.
Depth at sample point 6.9 feet; DO meter not calibrated before monitoring. Sampled at 43.54527- 89.10390.
